(# Zero to Hero Study Handbook: pytorch-distilbert-complaint-classifier) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Module 1: Foundations & Architecture) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 1.1 What This Project Does) Tj
T*
(This project fine-tunes DistilBERT to classify short banking support queries into 77 intent ) Tj
T*
(classes \(for example, `card_arrival`, `declined_transaction`, `extra_charge_on_statement`\), ) Tj
T*
(using the Banking77 dataset.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Primary use cases in this repository:) Tj
T*
(- Train and evaluate a transformer-based intent classifier end-to-end in a notebook workflow.) Tj
T*
(- Compare transformer performance against a classical baseline \(`TF-IDF + LogisticRegression`\).) Tj
T*
(- Run production-style CLI inference for single text or batch files via `inference.py`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The source of truth for the notebook content is `generate_notebook.py`, which generates ) Tj
T*
(`pytorch_distilbert_complaint_classifier.ipynb`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 1.2 Core Paradigms and Patterns Used Here) Tj
T*
(Definitions first, then where they appear:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. **Supervised multi-class classification**) Tj
T*
(The model maps one input text to exactly one label among 77 classes.) Tj
T*
(Where: notebook code generated in `generate_notebook.py` \(`NUM_LABELS`, `id2label`, ) Tj
T*
(`label2id`\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. **Transfer learning / fine-tuning**) Tj
T*
(A pretrained language model \(`distilbert-base-uncased`\) is adapted to this specific intent task) Tj
T*
( with a new classification head.) Tj
T*
(Where: `build_model\(\)` in generated notebook code.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. **Functional pipeline style**) Tj
T*
(Processing is split into small functions that pass explicit data structures \(`set_seed`, ) Tj
T*
(`encode`, `make_optimizer`, `evaluate`, `metrics_from_logits`, notebook `predict`; and in CLI ) Tj
T*
(`load_model`, `read_inputs`, `predict`\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. **Configuration via dataclass**) Tj
T*
(Training hyperparameters and paths are centralized in `Config` dataclass \(for example ) Tj
T*
(`max_len`, `epochs`, `lr`, `warmup_ratio`, `ckpt_dir`, `fig_dir`\).) Tj
T*
(Where: generated notebook code in `generate_notebook.py`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. **Artifact-contract pattern**) Tj
T*
(Training produces artifacts consumed by inference:) Tj
T*
(- `checkpoints/best_model.pt` \(raw PyTorch checkpoint dict\)) Tj
T*
(- `checkpoints/best_model/` \(HuggingFace `save_pretrained` directory for model+tokenizer\)) Tj
T*
(Inference loads `checkpoints/best_model/` by default.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. **Selective prediction pattern**) Tj
T*
(The notebook evaluates confidence-based routing \(coverage vs. accuracy\) to support human ) Tj
T*
(fallback on low-confidence predictions.) Tj
T*
(Where: confidence analysis section in generated notebook code.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 1.3 Architecture Description \(Components + Interactions\)) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
