(## Module 4: Setup & Run Guide) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1 Clean-Machine Prerequisites) Tj
T*
(- Shell context: README commands are provided in bash style.) Tj
T*
(- Python: `3.12.10` \(from `.python-version`, and `>=3.12.10` in `pyproject.toml`\).) Tj
T*
(- Package/tool manager: `uv` \(project is configured for `uv` workflow\).) Tj
T*
(- Optional acceleration: NVIDIA GPU \(CUDA 12.8 wheel index configured for torch\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.2 Dependency Installation) Tj
T*
(Typical sequence from README:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```bash) Tj
T*
(git clone https://github.com/pypi-ahmad/pytorch-distilbert-complaint-classifier.git) Tj
T*
(cd pytorch-distilbert-complaint-classifier) Tj
T*
(uv sync) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What `uv sync` uses:) Tj
T*
(- `pyproject.toml` dependency list:) Tj
T*
(  - `torch`, `transformers`, `datasets`, `accelerate`, `numpy`, `pandas`, `scikit-learn`, ) Tj
T*
(  `matplotlib`, `seaborn`, `jupyter`, `ipykernel`, `nbformat`, `tqdm`) Tj
T*
(- `tool.uv` torch source override:) Tj
T*
(  - `pytorch-cu128` index \(`https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128`\)) Tj
T*
